        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/map-foreign-relations-flags.jpg" alt="A world map showing flags of the US, UK, Colombia, Egypt, Sudan, and Palestine pinpointed across their respective regions, illustrating international relations or diplomatic focus." href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              padding-top: 0px;
              padding-bottom: 6px;
            ">
          <strong>🇸🇩 Sudan - Sudanese refugees return.</strong> Many Sudanese refugees in Egypt are returning home under Egypt's voluntary return programme, despite the ongoing conflict. Hardship in Egypt and the army's recent recapture of key areas, including Khartoum and Al-Jazirah, are driving the returns. Meanwhile, many continue to flee their homeland, which has been ravaged by war and famine (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-jul-25-worldwide-10-homecoming-hardships?source=website" target="_blank">homecoming hardships</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
          <strong>🇺🇸 USA - Trump rules out summit.</strong> President Trump denied wanting a summit with Chinese President Xi Jinping and termed it “fake news.” Trump said he was open to visiting China if invited, but he is not actively seeking a meeting. Meanwhile, ongoing trade talks between the US and China in Stockholm could lead to a tariff truce and a possible future summit, as the August tariff deadlines approach (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-jul-25-worldwide-11-trade-talks?source=website" target="_blank">trade talks</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
        <strong>🇬🇧 UK - Plans to recognize Palestine.</strong> PM Keir Starmer announced the UK will recognize a Palestinian state at September’s UN General Assembly unless Israel takes constructive steps toward peace. The move follows France’s similar commitment and comes amid the deteriorating Gaza crisis. Starmer also demands that Hamas disarm and release the hostages (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-jul-25-worldwide-12-strong-stance?source=website" target="_blank">strong stance</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
       <strong>🇨🇴 Colombia - Ex-president convicted.</strong> Former Colombian President Álvaro Uribe was convicted of witness tampering, becoming the first ex-head of state in Colombia to face a criminal conviction. He attempted to bribe a paramilitary to retract his testimony linking him to armed groups. Uribe faces up to 12 years in prison and argues the conviction is political vengeance (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-jul-25-worldwide-13-presidential-convictions?source=website" target="_blank">presidential convictions</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
       <strong>🇩🇪 Germany- Humanitarian aid drop.</strong> German Chancellor Friedrich Merz announced that two German A400M aircraft will start airdropping humanitarian aid to Gaza from Jordan.  Speaking with Jordan’s King Abdullah, Merz stressed the mission's symbolic and practical importance. He welcomed Israel’s initial steps to allow aid but said more measures are needed (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-07-2025-german-airdrops?source=website" target="_blank">German airdrops</a>).
